message: fixed hw wh bug in random crop

update the whl file

StepLR_Restart fixed by https://github.com/BlueAmulet
Change format and fix some typos

Update README.md

Updated readme for pip
re-added the sample benchmark Notebook, might be useful for testing
commiting new loss builder, to be reused in all models
adding the optimizer and scheduler builders and the modified model and training files to make use of all the changes. Updated the train options file with all the new options

added using discriminator feature maps for feature loss as an alternative/complement to other pretrained classification networks like VGG or LPIPS (using the discriminator_vgg_128_fea discriminator model)
update readme with more info on changes
multiple fixes for compatibility between pytorch 1.6.0 (Colab) and 1.3.0, Automatic Mixed Precision (AMP) properly integrated and tested, one temporary fix while AMP bug is being investigated
mention added support for YAML in changes
mentioning patchgan in readme and added correct paper reference, added yaml recompiler to parse scientific notation like json
now possible to read blur and noise augmentations as a dictionary, list or single string
modifications and new options for the color transfer script
WIP commit of the video SR architecture based on SOF-VSR. Includes network, model, dataloader, loss, inference and training codes. To be tested.
stricter frameskip check to prevent list out of boundary
merged dataset tester code into existing test_dataloader.py, added WIP PBR dataloader for testing
modify video dataloader, network and model to work with 3ch images, add option to use different image upscaling networks with the HR optical flow estimation for video
WIP: initial commit of the RIFE architecture, simplified into a single nn.Module for testing
add option to freeze initial discriminator layers for faster training/transfer learning using pretrained discriminators
Add 3D convolution for Video ESRGAN architecture
Added pretrained EVSRGAN model to README
added SR3D architecture using Conv3D and temporal feature maps, removed the conditional slicing in RRDB
Update readme files, Add badges for Python ver, License, DeepSource, Issues, and PRs Welcome
add mention of chop forward and link to DVD pretrained models in readme
include detailed instructions to use KernelGAN estimated kernels for training
add SRFlow architecture, model, train and test options files and Glow required files. Updated readme and archs doc

update (some) transforms to use common classes (more TBS), add cv2 k-means based color quantization (RandomQuantize), add option to compress images with webp or jpeg, expose bilateral filter transform, add ApplyKernel for convolving with arbitrary kernels (motion, KernelGAN, others), add simple and complex motion blur transforms with randomly generated motion kernels (RandomMotionBlur, RandomComplexMotionBlur), adopt process in chunks, CLAHE and use of function wrappers from albumentations
update train and test instructions, add sponsorship options
small update for video and pbr dataloader to continue working, updated lr_downscale types in video training options file, other small fixes

add Superpixels augmentation, support for CV2 and skimage superpixel algorithms (multiple slic, seeds, felzenszwalb), custom label2rgb adaptive function, 3 segmentation reduction options (selective search, k-means cluster, RAG), update gamma_adjust function and add RandomGamma transformation, add functions for srgb<->linear transformations
added workaround to disable Intel Fortran Control+C console event handler installed by scipy, updated readme
update files to reflect new repo name, from 'BasicSR' to 'traiNNer'

added even image size correction to camera unprocess pipeline (for mosaic operation), added scale factor for Poisson noise type by extracting the correlated noise from the corrupted image and readding it with the scale factor, adapted sinc filter augmentation
update change to sr_model module, minor documentation updates
add AdaTarget option for adaptive model output generation and initial required changes to use. Small doc updates
